1
00:00:00,440 --> 00:00:02,210
[RECAP]
And so begins

2
00:00:02,210 --> 00:00:04,100
a battle with the Yamamoto-family honor on the line.

3
00:00:04,100 --> 00:00:07,020
The Yamamoto-family Big Brother Quick Buzzer Quiz!

4
00:00:07,020 --> 00:00:09,020
Let's get right into question one!

5
00:00:09,020 --> 00:00:14,210
Honoka Hayami and Chihiro Yamamoto have had a steady relationship up until now.

6
00:00:14,210 --> 00:00:19,200
What unbelievable incident befell them recently?

7
00:00:19,200 --> 00:00:20,740
Yes, Masami, you buzzed in first!

8
00:00:20,740 --> 00:00:26,730
For some reason, a man other than Chihiro visited Hayami's family home as her boyfriend!

9
00:00:26,730 --> 00:00:27,970
Ta-daaa!

10
00:00:27,970 --> 00:00:32,750
Congrats on your serious relationship!

11
00:00:32,750 --> 00:00:35,090
- However!
- What?!

12
00:00:35,090 --> 00:00:41,040
What common issue amongst couples came up as a result of that?

13
00:00:41,040 --> 00:00:42,160
Yes, Kaoru?

14
00:00:42,160 --> 00:00:46,590
The "who likes the other person more" problem, right?

15
00:00:46,590 --> 00:00:50,580
I won't say "it's always me." I like you more than you do.

16
00:00:50,580 --> 00:00:53,120
I may not look it,

17
00:00:53,120 --> 00:00:57,380
but I lo-love you.

18
00:00:57,380 --> 00:00:59,600
I love you!

19
00:00:59,600 --> 00:01:02,870
- However!
- Again?

20
00:01:02,870 --> 00:01:06,640
Upon feeling as though she hasn't gotten her love completely across,

21
00:01:06,640 --> 00:01:11,540
what surprising final act does Honoka perform?

22
00:01:13,530 --> 00:01:15,980
[Answer]

23
00:01:17,690 --> 00:01:20,360
It doesn't matter who likes each other more

24
00:01:20,360 --> 00:01:23,080
or who wins,

25
00:01:23,910 --> 00:01:27,260
but I want you to actually feel it.

26
00:01:30,250 --> 00:01:33,100
That you're loved.

27
00:01:43,230 --> 00:01:45,560
Understood.

28
00:01:45,560 --> 00:01:50,100
Um, I feel very much loved, so I'm fine now.

29
00:01:50,100 --> 00:01:52,080
But

30
00:01:52,080 --> 00:01:54,540
I haven't done anything yet.

31
00:01:54,540 --> 00:01:57,950
No, really! I'm fine.

32
00:02:00,800 --> 00:02:05,680
Oh, don't get the wrong idea! It's not that I don't want to kiss you.

33
00:02:05,680 --> 00:02:08,560
Then why?

34
00:02:10,480 --> 00:02:13,490
Well,

35
00:02:14,110 --> 00:02:17,460
how far are you prepared to go from here?

36
00:02:23,650 --> 00:02:24,750
Sorry.

37
00:02:24,750 --> 00:02:27,390
[Chihiro Yamamoto - Raccoon Electronics Sales Department
Honoka Hayami - Raccoon Electronics Sales Department]

38
00:02:27,390 --> 00:02:29,090
Right?

39
00:02:29,090 --> 00:02:30,810
Look.

40
00:02:30,810 --> 00:02:32,270
It's fine.

41
00:02:32,270 --> 00:02:35,930
I don't ever want to become that scumbag guy again

42
00:02:35,930 --> 00:02:38,120
who forces himself onto you when you don't want to.

43
00:02:38,120 --> 00:02:39,960
No,

44
00:02:39,960 --> 00:02:41,740
that's not it.

45
00:02:41,740 --> 00:02:45,060
- I did want to, but...
- What?

46
00:02:45,060 --> 00:02:48,680
When I tried to imagine it...

47
00:02:49,820 --> 00:02:53,960
I felt that it'd be embarrassing doing it at home.

48
00:02:54,960 --> 00:02:58,020
Maybe it's because we were already living together before we started dating.

49
00:02:58,020 --> 00:03:00,880
The daily grind just feels too real.

50
00:03:00,880 --> 00:03:04,140
It's hard to switch the mindset from that.

51
00:03:05,520 --> 00:03:08,770
Wait, am I the only one who feels this way?

52
00:03:11,390 --> 00:03:16,550
Argh, give me a break.

53
00:03:19,460 --> 00:03:21,440
Honestly.

54
00:03:22,270 --> 00:03:24,720
You make things so hard for me.

55
00:03:26,530 --> 00:03:28,730
Um,

56
00:03:28,730 --> 00:03:31,890
did I get my love across properly just now?

57
00:03:36,200 --> 00:03:37,610
Yes.

58
00:03:41,720 --> 00:03:44,120
'Yes' is what I said, but...

59
00:03:44,120 --> 00:03:46,840
that means we can't do it at home, doesn't it?

60
00:03:46,840 --> 00:03:48,650
But if home's out of the question

61
00:03:48,650 --> 00:03:50,430
then where? Outside? In the open?

62
00:03:50,430 --> 00:03:53,570
No, that has to be beyond embarrassing.

63
00:03:53,570 --> 00:03:55,690
So then a hotel?

64
00:03:55,690 --> 00:03:58,040
A hotel. Hmm.

65
00:03:58,040 --> 00:04:01,450
That'll make me seem way too eager.

66
00:04:01,450 --> 00:04:03,300
Huh, then where do we--

67
00:04:04,740 --> 00:04:06,980
Koga!

68
00:04:06,980 --> 00:04:08,080
[Iori Koga - Raccoon Electronics Sales Department]

69
00:04:08,080 --> 00:04:10,060
Uh, what you heard just now was...

70
00:04:10,060 --> 00:04:12,850
It's okay. I'll pretend I heard nothing.

71
00:04:14,160 --> 00:04:15,540
Sorry.

72
00:04:15,540 --> 00:04:19,870
Honestly, all I cause you is trouble.

73
00:04:19,870 --> 00:04:22,380
Hayami, I...

74
00:04:22,380 --> 00:04:25,080
want to talk to you for a little...

75
00:04:28,030 --> 00:04:31,060
Um,

76
00:04:31,060 --> 00:04:35,020
there's no real deep meaning to this,

77
00:04:38,750 --> 00:04:42,720
but how do you feel

78
00:04:43,900 --> 00:04:46,810
towards Hayami?

79
00:04:46,810 --> 00:04:50,140
What do you mean by that?

80
00:04:50,140 --> 00:04:52,770
Actually, it's okay. Sorry.

81
00:04:52,770 --> 00:04:56,260
- What?
- Really, it's nothing.

82
00:04:57,670 --> 00:05:00,490
I see. Okay, I'm off, then.

83
00:05:00,490 --> 00:05:01,860
Right.

84
00:05:06,980 --> 00:05:08,700
Yamamoto.

85
00:05:10,040 --> 00:05:14,470
You must treasure your partner's feelings more than anything else.

86
00:05:16,110 --> 00:05:17,470
I will.

87
00:05:24,180 --> 00:05:29,050
Phew, that's Koga for you. There's no topping him.

88
00:05:29,980 --> 00:05:31,440
That's what you're thinking, huh?

89
00:05:31,440 --> 00:05:32,760
[Ryo Kasuga - Raccoon Electronics Sales Department]

90
00:05:32,760 --> 00:05:34,650
No, I don't!

91
00:05:34,650 --> 00:05:36,030
Wait, how long have you been standing there?

92
00:05:36,030 --> 00:05:37,970
I just got here.

93
00:05:38,640 --> 00:05:42,480
Here. The chief told me to hand these out to everyone.

94
00:05:42,480 --> 00:05:43,880
Oh.

95
00:05:45,730 --> 00:05:47,810
An in-house contest to develop a new product?

96
00:05:47,810 --> 00:05:52,570
The company wants to gather ideas for new products from staff, regardless of their department.

97
00:05:52,570 --> 00:05:54,210
[Katsunori Sasaki - Raccoon Electronics Sales Chief]
I see.

98
00:05:54,210 --> 00:05:57,300
The winning prize is pretty impressive.

99
00:05:57,300 --> 00:06:00,650
It's a trip for two to Okinawa!

100
00:06:00,650 --> 00:06:03,330
Wow, that is impressive.

101
00:06:03,330 --> 00:06:05,270
I heard Yamamoto's going to submit something.

102
00:06:05,270 --> 00:06:07,280
He is?

103
00:06:07,280 --> 00:06:09,930
When I gave one of these to him the look in his eyes changed.

104
00:06:09,930 --> 00:06:14,630
He actually wanted to be part of the Planning and Development department when he first joined the company.

105
00:06:14,630 --> 00:06:17,080
- Really?
- Good for him!

106
00:06:17,080 --> 00:06:22,040
He could transfer into the Planning and Development department if he does well in the contest.

107
00:06:22,040 --> 00:06:23,170
[Reina Akamine - Raccoon Electronics Personnel Department]
He most certainly could.

108
00:06:23,170 --> 00:06:27,810
Yamamoto is vying for the Okinawa trip to go with Honoka?
[Ran Hanazuma - Raccoon Electronics Sales Department]

109
00:06:27,810 --> 00:06:31,680
That's right. He apparently had dreams for product development.

110
00:06:31,680 --> 00:06:36,960
His real goal is the trip to Okinawa so he can go with Hayami!

111
00:06:37,650 --> 00:06:41,440
That'll make him a complete perv, no doubt about it!

112
00:06:41,440 --> 00:06:43,900
Super excited atop a bed?!

113
00:06:43,900 --> 00:06:45,690
But wait a moment.

114
00:06:45,690 --> 00:06:47,790
We don't have the right to stop them--

115
00:06:47,790 --> 00:06:50,930
You're not talking like the super-lover boy you are!

116
00:06:50,930 --> 00:06:55,890
Weren't you the one decided to do your best to draw Hayami's attention towards you?!

117
00:06:55,890 --> 00:06:57,970
H-How do you know--

118
00:06:57,970 --> 00:07:01,130
There's nothing I don't know about Hayami.

119
00:07:01,130 --> 00:07:03,190
- You're incredible!
- In any case!

120
00:07:03,190 --> 00:07:07,120
We're entering the contest too!

121
00:07:07,120 --> 00:07:09,020
I see.

122
00:07:09,020 --> 00:07:13,030
I'm the one who's going on the winning trip to Okinawa with Hayami!

123
00:07:13,030 --> 00:07:14,950
Or it'll be me!

124
00:07:14,950 --> 00:07:16,600
Or perhaps!

125
00:07:16,600 --> 00:07:18,900
Koga! You!

126
00:07:18,900 --> 00:07:21,830
- What?
- Is this okay with you?

127
00:07:21,830 --> 00:07:26,320
At this rate, the two of them with come to work with matching Okinawan T-shirts

128
00:07:26,320 --> 00:07:28,960
and become a loved-up dimwitted couple!

129
00:07:28,960 --> 00:07:31,920
I suppose that might bug me.

130
00:07:31,920 --> 00:07:35,730
Then you must enter the contest too!

131
00:07:35,730 --> 00:07:38,120
I was already planning to enter to begin with.

132
00:07:38,120 --> 00:07:39,730
Oh, is that so?

133
00:07:39,730 --> 00:07:44,930
The Planning and Development department chief asked me directly. There's no way I can refuse.

134
00:07:44,930 --> 00:07:48,200
A direct request from the Planning and Development department?

135
00:07:48,200 --> 00:07:50,540
I can always depend on you, Koga!

136
00:07:51,770 --> 00:07:55,980
This all but guarantees your defeat, Yamamoto.

137
00:07:55,980 --> 00:07:57,530
Akamine?

138
00:07:57,530 --> 00:08:00,190
You should probably get back to focusing on work.

139
00:08:02,750 --> 00:08:04,150
I had no idea

140
00:08:04,150 --> 00:08:07,770
that you had an interest in product development.

141
00:08:07,770 --> 00:08:10,860
I've still got a lot to learn in the sales department

142
00:08:10,860 --> 00:08:14,680
so I figured I shouldn't be rambling about such fantasies.

143
00:08:14,680 --> 00:08:18,930
But a chance like this doesn't come often, so...

144
00:08:18,930 --> 00:08:20,370
Yeah, I think it's great.

145
00:08:20,370 --> 00:08:23,360
You're not entering the contest?

146
00:08:24,540 --> 00:08:30,260
I like sales work.

147
00:08:31,810 --> 00:08:36,460
I mean, I can't create a 'one' from a 'zero.'

148
00:08:36,460 --> 00:08:41,830
But I can do my best to show clients how good that 'one' is.

149
00:08:41,830 --> 00:08:45,340
Then the people who use it will gain joy from that.

150
00:08:45,340 --> 00:08:50,150
I can take that feedback with me and help the 'one' that was created to become

151
00:08:50,150 --> 00:08:54,960
a 'two' or 'three.' That's the kind of thing that makes me happy.

152
00:08:54,960 --> 00:08:58,280
You really are amazing.

153
00:08:58,280 --> 00:08:59,990
That's why, one day,

154
00:08:59,990 --> 00:09:05,320
I hope to sell something you've developed like hot cakes. That'd be the best.

155
00:09:05,320 --> 00:09:07,700
Then I have to do my best.

156
00:09:07,700 --> 00:09:09,990
I'm cheering you on.

157
00:09:09,990 --> 00:09:13,150
Okay, I'm going to put away the things we've folded.

158
00:09:13,150 --> 00:09:14,750
Thanks.

159
00:09:33,230 --> 00:09:37,240
Chili bean sauce that's just so hard to finish.

160
00:09:40,720 --> 00:09:43,670
Socks that appear from under the sofa.

161
00:09:43,670 --> 00:09:46,360
The mountain of point cards that keeps growing.

162
00:09:47,350 --> 00:09:49,760
What kind of spell is that?

163
00:09:49,760 --> 00:09:54,640
I'm trying to calm myself down with menial every-day items. This is a home!

164
00:09:56,340 --> 00:09:58,240
If that's what you're worried about, you really don't have to--

165
00:09:58,240 --> 00:10:01,470
Honoka. I'm going to win that contest.

166
00:10:01,470 --> 00:10:05,090
Let's go to Okinawa, together!

167
00:10:06,220 --> 00:10:07,600
Okay.

168
00:10:37,300 --> 00:10:42,580
[MR. BRIDE, EPISODE 9]

169
00:10:42,580 --> 00:10:46,940
He's definitely resolved to get the first time done in Okinawa.

170
00:10:46,940 --> 00:10:49,290
[Kimiko Takahashi - Honoka's Friend]
Yeah.

171
00:10:49,290 --> 00:10:52,750
Why did I have to go and say that?!

172
00:10:52,750 --> 00:10:58,270
So you're the one who said you can't do it at home because it reminds you of the daily grind,

173
00:10:58,270 --> 00:11:00,240
yet you're actually sexually frustrated?

174
00:11:00,240 --> 00:11:01,840
No, that's not what I mean.

175
00:11:01,840 --> 00:11:04,920
I'm saying that Yamamoto is too considerate of me.

176
00:11:04,920 --> 00:11:06,210
So you're gushing about him to me?

177
00:11:06,210 --> 00:11:08,040
No, that's not it either.

178
00:11:08,040 --> 00:11:10,410
Well, that might be it, but--

179
00:11:10,410 --> 00:11:12,700
Oh, I'm glad you've acknowledged it.

180
00:11:16,000 --> 00:11:20,900
I want Yamamoto to focus on his own goals.

181
00:11:20,900 --> 00:11:26,530
Or rather, I'm thinking that I need to step up to help Yamamoto more

182
00:11:26,530 --> 00:11:28,450
as his girlfriend, you know?

183
00:11:30,290 --> 00:11:35,390
Then isn't there only one thing you can do for him?

184
00:11:46,500 --> 00:11:48,170
Good morning, Yamamoto.

185
00:11:48,170 --> 00:11:49,800
Good morning.

186
00:11:49,800 --> 00:11:50,980
What are you doing?

187
00:11:50,980 --> 00:11:55,860
You've got your regular sales work and you do all the housework, right?

188
00:11:55,860 --> 00:11:58,070
So you don't have any time to think about the contest, do you?

189
00:11:58,070 --> 00:12:01,420
That's why I figured I'd do the housework.

190
00:12:01,420 --> 00:12:03,230
- Um, but--
- It's okay.

191
00:12:03,230 --> 00:12:07,190
I can cook simple meals if you're not picky about flavors

192
00:12:07,190 --> 00:12:10,520
so you can rest your mind at ease and focus on the contest.

193
00:12:10,520 --> 00:12:12,050
Okay.

194
00:12:12,050 --> 00:12:14,370
Okay, but!

195
00:12:15,060 --> 00:12:17,970
They're really burnt! The eggs!

196
00:12:21,200 --> 00:12:23,410
I got it.

197
00:12:23,410 --> 00:12:27,750
He ended up re-cooking everything for me...

198
00:12:27,750 --> 00:12:29,910
What, really? I can have this?

199
00:12:29,910 --> 00:12:33,040
Of course! This is for everyone to share.

200
00:12:33,040 --> 00:12:35,330
Wow, this guaranteed to be tasty.

201
00:12:37,030 --> 00:12:38,520
You should have some too, Hayami.

202
00:12:44,030 --> 00:12:46,300
I'm Saori Miyashita, a food researcher.

203
00:12:46,300 --> 00:12:50,170
Miyashita's popular for the recipe videos she uploads online.

204
00:12:50,880 --> 00:12:52,630
Her ideas are so original.

205
00:12:52,630 --> 00:12:54,870
I'm going to use potato chips as the crumb

206
00:12:54,870 --> 00:12:58,480
to make non-fried double potato croquettes.

207
00:12:58,480 --> 00:13:01,650
The idea to coat potatoes with more potatoes is incredible, right?

208
00:13:01,650 --> 00:13:03,790
Indeed. It looks so delicious.

209
00:13:03,790 --> 00:13:07,110
And for our upcoming microwave sales promotion

210
00:13:07,110 --> 00:13:10,630
the plan is to use sweets created by Miyashita.

211
00:13:10,630 --> 00:13:13,690
- I see.
- Something smells really tasty.

212
00:13:13,690 --> 00:13:15,810
Hey, Yamamoto! Come and have some too.

213
00:13:15,810 --> 00:13:17,840
Ooh, really?

214
00:13:17,840 --> 00:13:19,480
Go ahead.

215
00:13:22,470 --> 00:13:24,200
Chihiro?

216
00:13:25,770 --> 00:13:27,320
Saori?

217
00:13:29,180 --> 00:13:31,600
Long time no see.

218
00:13:34,800 --> 00:13:35,400
How is it?

219
00:13:38,360 --> 00:13:41,180
No, that's not it...

220
00:13:41,180 --> 00:13:42,990
Say, Yamamoto?

221
00:13:42,990 --> 00:13:46,490
I didn't get a chance to ask you today, so...

222
00:13:46,490 --> 00:13:50,440
How exactly do you know Miyashita?

223
00:13:53,940 --> 00:13:58,550
I guess she was an acquaintance-ish person when I was in college?

224
00:13:58,550 --> 00:14:00,650
An acquaintance?

225
00:14:00,650 --> 00:14:03,510
You could say we were in the same class...

226
00:14:03,510 --> 00:14:05,290
So classmates.

227
00:14:07,390 --> 00:14:10,180
Sorry, she's my ex-girlfriend.

228
00:14:10,180 --> 00:14:12,280
I thought so. It could kinda sense it.

229
00:14:12,280 --> 00:14:16,000
But it's not what you think. We were only together for a bit.

230
00:14:16,000 --> 00:14:19,460
She said she didn't need two moms, so she dumped me.

231
00:14:20,080 --> 00:14:24,840
He got dumped by this ex-girlfriend because she said she didn't need two "mothers"!

232
00:14:24,840 --> 00:14:27,910
- Um...
- Yeah...

233
00:14:27,910 --> 00:14:32,770
I had no idea she'd become famous through her recipe videos.

234
00:14:37,540 --> 00:14:40,740
Oh, and I'll take care of cleaning up.

235
00:14:40,740 --> 00:14:45,060
No, it's okay. I might not be able to cook, so at least let me handle this.

236
00:14:45,060 --> 00:14:48,280
Don't go breaking any plates then!

237
00:14:48,280 --> 00:14:50,920
I'm not that clumsy.

238
00:14:52,040 --> 00:14:53,990
Look, what did I say?

239
00:14:53,990 --> 00:14:56,520
Hold up.

240
00:14:56,520 --> 00:14:59,400
I'll grab some things to clean up with, so don't touch any of that.

241
00:14:59,400 --> 00:15:01,560
It's dangerous.

242
00:15:01,560 --> 00:15:03,450
- Okay.
- Good.

243
00:15:06,930 --> 00:15:08,950
When I got home today

244
00:15:08,950 --> 00:15:11,250
the circuit breaker had been tripped for some reason...

245
00:15:11,250 --> 00:15:14,920
so everything inside of my freezer had been defrosted.

246
00:15:14,920 --> 00:15:18,170
So I'm going to use all of my thawed ingredients

247
00:15:18,170 --> 00:15:19,530
to make a week's worth

248
00:15:19,530 --> 00:15:23,140
- of food prep.
- I bet I'd be useful if I were a girlfriend like her.

249
00:15:23,140 --> 00:15:27,030
I'm going to try my best. Perhaps I'll add some broccoli too.

250
00:15:34,270 --> 00:15:36,480
Miyashita?

251
00:15:37,320 --> 00:15:39,170
Hayami!

252
00:15:41,610 --> 00:15:47,180
I've come up with a number of recipe ideas so I was hoping to perhaps get some feedback from Kasuga.

253
00:15:48,000 --> 00:15:51,920
Wow, you've already thought of so many in a day?

254
00:15:53,340 --> 00:15:58,750
We live in an era right now where anyone can release their own recipes.

255
00:15:58,750 --> 00:16:01,110
On social media and the like.

256
00:16:01,110 --> 00:16:07,300
So food researchers have to compete on their own ground, in a sense.

